\f0\fs28 \cf0 It is customary, according to the code of etiquette, to call all the hours of daylight morning, and after nightfall evening. In making a formal call, a lady does not remove her bonnet or wraps. A gentleman, making a formal call in the morning, must retain his hat in his hand. He may leave his umbrella and cane in the hall, but not his hat and gloves. The fact of retaining his hat indicates a formal call.\
When a gentleman accompanies a lady at a morning call (which is seldom), he assists her up the steps, rings the bell, and follows her into the reception room. It is for the lady to determine when they should leave.\
Calls from people living in the country are expected to be longer and less ceremonious than from those in the city.\
