\b \cf0 What Should Be Avoided When Calling\
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\li720\fi-720\sl288\slmult1\pardirnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\b0 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Do not stare around the room\
{\listtext	\'95	}Do not take a dog or small child.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Do not lay aside the bonnet at a formal call.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Do not fidget with your cane, hat, or parasol.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Do not make a call of ceremony on a wet day.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Do not touch the piano, unless invited to do so.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Do not handle ornaments or furniture in the room.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Do not make a display of consulting your watch.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Do not go to the room of an invalid, unless invited.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Do not continue the call longer when conversation begins to lag.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Do not remain when you find the lady upon the point of going out.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Do not open or shut doors or windows or alter the arrangement of the room.\
